not going home until tomorrow now becuase the snow decided to come a little earlier than expected! 
i even took my broadcast final early.  i couldve had more time to study but noooo.. it had to fucking snow.  
not to mention that everything is in my car at the moment, including the stuff that i need.  This fucking sucks. oh and im freezing becuase i spent the last 10 mintues trying to get shit out of my car.

im going to sleep. maybe when i wake up, it'll be tomorrow.

So I've been trapped inside this sickness cave that I call my room here at home for the past weekend.  Being sick is horrible.  And why do I always get sick during finals.  It's happened everytime since senior year when I had bronchitus. So I had to get out of the house..so me and my mom went shopping! For once, we didn't fight or anything and she just kept buying me stuff..it was great.  I'm the first person to admit that I'm a tad bit materialistic, but hey I'm a girl who knwos what she wants and gets it..enough said. So basically I'm getting like a gajillion peices of jewelry for Christmas including my wonderful Zales pearl and diamond set, some "fake" (jeez i hate that word) tiffany's jewelry and some pretty schnazzy other stuff.  And I'm getting this bag that I picked out at Details thats by this designer Melie Bianco.  The girls on Laguna Beach had like 31354681 bags by her.  I learned this after I picked it out lol.  
My sister came in on Saturday with Emar and the 2 puppies! It was the first time I got to see Jack and he's like the cutest pug you will ever see.  I wanted to steal him from her so bad.
I got to see Sugarland, Brad Paisley, and Sara Evans in concert on Thursday. It was great but I probably wouldve enjoyed it better if I wasnt sick.. and if my cowboy hat had come in on time.
So I'm going back to Ship tomorrow for my Government final and the party at Bill and Travis'.  I have a final on Thursday and a project due by the end of the week.  Have I done any work for anything?? That would be a negative. Not looking forward to the next 3 days..

So I'm here in Boston.  Everything's going great here.  Jill's doing fine..Her hair is starting to grow back which is good.  WE went to Fennial Hall today.  I bought two shirts in Banana REbublic (Nana Pubs as Jill calls it) and jewelry in this cool museum store.  Then we ate at the replica of the Cheers bar.  It was fun.  Then me , Jill, and my mom went to Burlingotn and I got an awesome pair of cowboy boots (I'm so cool) and these really cool sweater clogs..Theyre seriosuly the best things ever.  We all went to eat at Bertucci's, which is this really amazing Italian Resturaunt. (I'm so wearing my fat pants right now I ate so much).  Emar (aka Orlando..hsi code name) is burning me Mean Girls and I'm so psyched.  This whole wekend we've hadd this song stuck in our heads from the Diet Cherry Vanilla Dr. Pepper commercial...It's baaad. hahaha

Now were just playin with the pups and watching XMen 2.  Were coming back to PA tomorrow and I'm gunna be goin back to Ship on Monday after my hair appointment.  I can't wait to get my hair cut! haha.  I've been trying all weekend to work on my assignment for Broadcast Writing and serisouly can't do it..lol.  I really don't want to do it and I'm just not in the mood. Plus, I just hate my prof.  He's a dick.
In other news..I'm so happy that it's fall! I love fall.  The weather is just perfect. :) I can't wait til the leaves start to change...
2 weeks til Florida! Woo! It's gunna be amazing.

You're a Ravenpuff!: You are a very analytical and
ingenius person, someone that likes to invent
new things. The way you look at life is with
wonder, and sometimes you're even a little
naive. But people love you for that trait and
they feel the need to protect you from the
harsh facts of life so that you can retain your
innocence. You are very capable person and when
there is trouble people turn to you because
you're able to stay calm and collected. You
like balance in your life and you try not to
make many waves. Even still, if there is
something that you believe strongly in, you
will commit yourself totally to that cause.
Your weakness is that sometimes you can be
indecisive and perfectionist, especially about
little details and you drive people crazy
sometimes with these traits. With the innocence of a Hufflepuff and the calm of a
Ravenclaw you will be loved in life!

Your Birthdate: May 27
Your birth on the 27th day of the month (9 energy) adds a tone of selflessness and humanitarianism to your life path. Certainly, you are one who can work very well with people, but at the same time you need a good bit of time to be by yourself to rest and meditate. There is a very humanistic and philanthropic approach in most of things that you do. This birthday helps you be broadminded, tolerant, generous and very cooperative. You are the type of person who uses persuasion rather than force to achieve your ends. You tend to be very sensitive to others' needs and feelings, and you able to give much in the way of friendship without expecting a lot in return.

I was tagged by crazy_betty..

List ten fictional characters (not actors/actresses) you would want to have sex with and then tag five people. Any media (movies, books, video games, etc).

10. Rusty Ryan (Oceans Eleven and Twelve)-Brad Pitt in a nice suit makes my melt.  He's also just funny in a "I'm not trying to be funny, it just happens" kinda way.

9. Ben Barry (How to Lose a Guy In Ten Days)- Ok so he was an ass for making a bet at work..but they needed a plot line somewhere.  Theres just somehting about a guy with a southern accent and a really nice body.  Whoever gets Matthew McConaughey is one lucky woman.

8. Steve Hale (Full House)-  I just love Steve and his obsession with food and football--typical guy.  And I love the fact that Scott Wiegner is the voice of Aladdin(who almost made the list).  It makes me happy.

7. Ryan Atwood (The OC)- Hot but quiet.  He can tell you anything with just a stare.  And he's slowly becoming funnier-much to Seth's dismay. lol

6. JJ Pryor (American Dreams)- I love a man in uniform.  And his strong, stable personality in the show just stands out.  He loves his wife and his child more than anything in the world.  I'm not sure which JJ I like better-- pre-Vietman or post-Veitnam JJ.  But overall, he is a support system for the Pryors and his new family.

5. Cory Matthews (Boy Meets World)- I must agree with Katy on this one becuase I grew up loving Cory and envying Topanga.  I just love him more than words can describe.

4. Chris Peirce (American Dreams)- Played by none other than the fabulous Milo Ventimiglia.  Think Jess from Gilmore girls only make it back in the 1960's.  Enough said.

3. Micheal (Roswell)-  I was originally going to pick Max instead by Michael is just (honestly) so much more interesting than Max.  Theres just something about the bad boy that you just gotta love.  The uncontrollable nature of him makes him so exciting and I need a little excitement in my life.  But deep down he cared deeply for Maria whether he wanted to admit it or not.

2. Seth Cohen (The O.C.)- Ok we all know why Seth is number one---if you dont you dont deserve to be my friend..seriosuly.  I love guys who can make me laugh and no one can resist his dorky charm.

1. Noah Calhoun (The Notebook)- I consider this oe of the greatest love stories of our time told perfectly in Nicholas Sparks' book and performed even better by Ryan Gosling.  Noah's just so down to Earth, loving, and caring that he would be the perfect guy.  Plus the way that he always remained in love with Allie through everything and always believed in their love would make any girl want a man like him.

This may sound very stupid or strange to some of you, but today I feel as if a part of me has died along with Peter Jennings, who has been one of my heroes and idols in the broadcasting world.  His voice, his charisma, and his talent have had a lasting impact on my life and what kind of journalist I want to be.  
I think thats its better that he wasnt on the air for the last four months.  At least the shock of him suddenly not being there wont be a problem.  But I will certainly miss the man who I turned to when I needed to know what was going on in the world. And I know Im not the only one who will miss him.

RIP Peter Jennings 8.7.2005

So..I'm home. For the summer.  But for some reason (even though ALL of my crap is currently scattered around my house) I just feel like I'm here for the weekend and then I'm supposed to drive back down to Ship on Monday.  I guess that's just becuase that's what I'm used to doing.  What I'm not used to are my parents.  Already I've had a little "fight" with my dad..but I guess that can be expected.  So tomorrow will consist of going through all of my scattered crap and putting things away.  Weird. 
I already miss having Hope across the hall from me.  and I'm gunna miss everyone greatly, but theres always next year for the vast amjority of my friends.

The year as a whole went by soo fast..even thogugh it was off to a slow start at first.  I made it thru marching band (lol) and History w/ Reber.  And living with a roommate. And I joined a wonderful organization that is SUTV and NBS.  I got to go to L-freakin-A!  I became a sister in the best damn music fraternity EVER! And through all this I got to meet some of the coolest people in the world.  Some are sadly graduating and to be honest I feel kinda jipped that I didnt get to spend more time with them.  I did meet some boys.  :) But unfortunatly I guess I'm just not good enough..But as I said before theres always next year for the rest of my friends.  

This year I think I accomplished soo much.  I got "re-invent" myself to the person that I really am.  I think I stepped out of my shell a bit. (THANK GOD!) And I feel very proud of everythign that I was able to do..especially as a freshman.  

I can't wait for next year-especially the apartment! But now I just need to spend some good old time with my friends from the valley--my girls-Katy, Tiff, Val, and Mary.  I need some of their lovin right about now. lol.  And hopefully I'll get to see some other ppl a lot too--*ahem* Mollie *ahem*.  

But right now I'm spent and I can't wait to not share a room and to sleep in my own, wonderful, big bed!!!  Night all.
